node.title: Man accused of raping Brittany Higgins at Parliament House committed to stand trial
node.alt: Bruce Lehrmann holds a trophy, standing next to an Australian flag in an office within Parliament House.
node.description: Bruce Lehrmann, the man accused of raping former Liberal staffer Brittany Higgins inside Parliament House, is committed for trial in the ACT Supreme Court.
node.content:
["The man accused of raping Brittany Higgins inside an office in Parliament House in 2019, will stand trial in the ACT Supreme Court.", "Bruce Lehrmann, 26, has pleaded not guilty to the charge.", "Today, he appeared in the ACT Magistrates Court by telephone.", "The ACT's Director of Public Prosecutions, Shane Drumgold, has indicated for some time that the brief of evidence is ready, and the case could be committed to the Supreme Court for trial.", "But Mr Lehrmann's lawyers had asked for more time, telling the court they had been unable to meet face to face with their client\u00a0to consult him about the case, because of COVID-19 restrictions.", "Mr Lehrmann has been in Queensland.", "He was charged and summonsed to appear in court after a lengthy police investigation earlier this year, which was prompted by a complaint by Ms Higgins.", "", "
Brittany Higgins\u00a0alleges she was raped at Parliament House in 2019.(AAP: Dean Lewins)
", "Today the case was committed for trial in the Supreme Court, with a first mention expected later this month.", "Any trial is unlikely until sometime next year."]
